    <h2>What is JAVA?</h2>
    <dl>
        <dt><dd>Java is a popular programming language, created in 1995.</dd></dt><br>
        <dd>It is owned by Oracle, and more than <b>3 billion </b>devices run Java.</dd><br>
        <dd>It is used for:</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul type="circle">
            <dd><li>Mobile applications <i>(specially Android apps)</i></li></dd>
            <dd><li>Desktop applications</li></dd>
            <dd><li>Web applications</li></dd>
            <dd><li>Games </li></dd>
            <dd><li>Database connection </li></dd>
    </ul>
    <h2>Why JAVA Use?</h2>
    <ol type="a">
        <dd><li>Java works on different platforms <cite>(Windows, Mac, Linux, Raspberry Pi, etc.)</cite></li></dd>
            <dd><li>It has huge community support <cite>(tens of millions of developers)</cite></li></dd>
            <dd><li>It is open-source and free</li></dd>
            <dd><li>It is secure, fast and powerful</li></dd>
            <dd><li>As Java is close to <ins>C++</ins> and <ins>C#</ins>, it makes it easy for programmers to switch to Java or vice versa </li></dd>
    </ol>
